Privacy Policy for Screen Time Monitor
Effective Date: 28-December-2024

Screen Time Monitor is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our Chrome extension.

1. Information We Collect
We only collect data necessary for the extension to function as intended:

Web History: We collect information about the websites you visit (e.g., URL, page title, and time spent) to calculate and display your screen time statistics.
User Activity: We track the currently active tab to provide accurate, real-time screen time monitoring.
We do not collect personally identifiable information (PII), passwords, or any sensitive data.

2. How We Use Your Information
The collected data is used solely for:

Calculating and displaying your screen time usage.
Sending you alerts based on your pre-set screen time limits.
All data is processed locally on your device and is not transmitted to any external servers.

3. Data Storage
The extension uses local storage on your browser to save preferences and usage data. This ensures that your information stays on your device.
4. Sharing Your Information
We do not share, sell, or distribute your data to third parties.

5. Data Security
We use industry-standard practices to safeguard your data. However, no system can guarantee absolute security.

6. Your Control
You can delete your usage data at any time by clearing the browserâ€™s local storage.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in the extension listing.

8. Contact Us
